This paper deals with sentiment analysis or opinion mining, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses lexical-based methods for sentiment classification, which involves using pre-defined lexicons and dictionaries, making it relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses semantic orientation, which is a concept in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
